Text:
Sublocade injection necrotic reaction awareness. Doctors are seeing necrotic wounds develop after sublocade injection. It's goes necrotic within 24 hours and can progress much worse to the need of wound debridement. My doctor now has 3 patients who have developed a necrotic wound at injection site. He said that he has heard this from other colleagues as well. 

&#x200B;

Now about myself and this issue. I have been on subloacde since the end of last April. I have now developed my 2nd necrotic wound from the injection on my abdomen. I was told it is an adverse reaction to the medication. This is one of the worst things that can happen to me. The last one took 4 months to heal, leaving behind a pink scar that is slowly shrinking. I want to mention as well, I am very lean and muscular, the other patient my dr mentioned was a female adult. So it doesn't seem to be an issue with the amount of fatty tissue. It is so unfortunate because it makes me afraid to date having this huge wound on my stomach.

Close of Day 7 and I still have insomnia but it doesn't feel like RESTLESS insomnia.. I know a lot of addicts probably know what I'm talking about with the restlessness. It's like this uncomfortable fizzy feeling you get in your muscles and makes it where you can't keep still because it feels like there's pent-up energy in them or something. That seems to be gone tonight. I just feel...well, not sleepy like I usually do around this time. My legs feel a lot better than they did earlier in the day, too. I'd had a lingering kind of achiness in my calves and ankles and it seems extremely minimal now. I'm thirsty a lot of the time, and it seems like only water really quenches my thirst decently. I've been hopping back and forth between drinking Body Armor juice to keep up vitamins and minerals and drinking water and it seems like even though the Body Armor is used for hydration it makes me feel thirstier.

&#x200B;

It seems like my posts are getting shorter which means I've got less to complain about so I guess it's a good sign.

My testosterone level is 239 which is normal for an 80 year old. Im 30. I take 6mg sub/day for 1 year. If I drop down to 2mg sub daily, will my T level/sex/drive increase with the reduced suboxone dose?. Didnt realize how bad my blood work results were. **Would dropping my dose to 2mg or even 1mg a day give any notable increase** or do I have to entirely quit suboxone? I don't want to quit it entirely, in a way I feel I am not ready to live "sober" or "drug free". Ill freely admit Suboxone is a crutch to me and mentally, I feel better with it in my daily routine. Going without it I don't feel confident.

&#x200B;

My spouse hates suboxone however due the effects of my lowered hormonal levels. 

&#x200B;

I read on google that 1mg of Bupe is equal to 75mg of Morphine. If that is true, Im taking about 450mg a day of morphine. I guess that explains the complete lack of sex drive/sexual desire? I have literally none.

&#x200B;
